## Results

> `row / col` == row's median tok/s ÷ col's median tok/s — i.e. "row is $N\times$ as
> fast as col". Values > 1 mean row is faster than col.

```elixir
results
|> Enum.map(&Summary.to_markdown/1)
|> Enum.join("\n\n---\n\n")
|> Kino.Markdown.new()
```

```elixir
results
|> Summary.stats_rows()
|> Kino.DataTable.new(name: "Per-lane tok/s stats")
```

